      {
        "text": "Shipping could be faster/cheaper. Had to add more coolant when I reseved it... It was about half full with coolant. To fix this I drilled two 2,5 mm holes in the top of the rear end tank, tapped the hole for a M.3 thread, filled with some 50/50 water and carcoolant. So, I would recommend giving the unit a good shake tho check if its full or low before powering on! I almost killed the pump! Other than that, the cooler works really well! Cools a 14600KF running 5.5GHz P cores - 3,9 E cores, no problem cooling spikes up too 240-250w from the CPU. If this comes up for sale with free shipping, I am probably going to buy another!",
